NAME

Lingua::EN::Numbers::Cardinal

SYNOPSIS
Convert integer numbers to their cardinal representation.

     use Lingua::EN::Numbers::Cardinal;

     say cardinal(1776); # one thousand, seven hundred seventy six
     say cardinal-year(1776) # seventeen-seventy-six


DESCRIPTION

Returns cardinal representations of integers following the American
English, short scale convention. The word "and" is only used to signify
fractional portions of a number. Since cardinal does not (yet) support
fractional numbers, "and" will not be inserted.

See also L<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_and_short_scales>

Exports subs cardinal() and cardinal-year().

cardinal() converts an integer or something that can be converted to
an integer to its cardinal representation.

Recognizes integer numbers from:
-9999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999
99999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999
99999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999
9999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999
to
99999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999
99999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999
99999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999
999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999999

