Should cover most uses.

cardinal-year() converts integers from 100 to 9999 to the common American
English convention.
2015 -> twenty-fifteen.
1984 -> nineteen-eighty-four.
Even millenniums are returned as thousands: 2000 -> two-thousand.
Even centuries are returned as hundreds: 1900 -> nineteen-hundred.
Years 1 .. 9 in each century are returned as oughts: 2001 -> twenty-ought-one.


BUGS

Expects integer numbers. If you feed it something other than an integer, do not
expect sensible results. Does some cursory error trapping but the foot cannon
is still loaded.


AUTHOR

